}{}$o({M_d}( i ),{M_d}( j ))$\end{document} the number of binding peaks containing CREs of both the motifs in the dataset. We select motif pairs with an Sc ≥ α as co-occurring motif pairs (CPs) for further analysis. The cutoff α is chosen such that the predicted motifs are maximally excluded, and at the same time, those in known CRMs are maximally included. Then for each pair of datasets a and b, we compute a similarity score Ss between each pair of CPs P[Ma(i), Ma(j)] from a and P[Mb (m), Mb (n)] from b, defined as,
